"...Chi-chan, would you like something to drink?" [l][r]
Chi-chan was standing by the window, helplessly looking up at the night sky. There was no moon in front of her. It was pitch black, and there was only darkness where you could only see a few stars. [l][r]

[r] "...I don't need it." [l][r]
It was a hollow-shelled reply. I sat down next to Chi-chan in silence and put my hands together. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[bg  time="1000"  method="crossfade"  storage="hand2.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
The hand twitches. I feel relieved that Chi-chan is still in good health. [l][r]

[r] "...I finally understand." [l][r]
"What?" [l][r]
"Why am I so unfulfilled?" [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
Chi-chan started talking like a machine. I silently intertwined my fingers to listen to it. [l][r]
[r] "This place is... too full. There's food. There's people. There's a place to live. There's a way to contact people even if they're far away. [l][r]
It's so convenient that it's unimaginable in the other world. [l][r]
[r]But... on the contrary, it makes me narrow-minded."[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

